Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_disable...ional_blocking(25.10)  timing_disable...ional_blocking(25.10)

Name
       timing_disable_genclk_combinational_blocking

Syntax
       timing_disable_genclk_combinational_blocking

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Disables blocking of the latency path for a generated clock.

       When  set  to true, allows the latency path to traverse through the up-
       stream generated clock.

       When set to false, if two back-to-back generated clocks are on the same
       path, and if the downstream generated  clock  is  set  using  the  cre-
       ate_generated_clock -combinational parameter, then the latency path for
       this  generated  clock is blocked by the upstream clock. The downstream
       generated clock is created with zero latency.

       The software shows a warning if the source latency path to the upstream
       generated clock cannot be found. For example,

       **WARN: (TA-1018): A source latency path to  the  generated  clock  GC2
       through  source  pin  clk1  to  target pin GC2_1/Y in view default_emu-
       late_view cannot be found. Timing analysis will use 0 ns source latency
       for the generated clock and will interpret the master  clock  based  on
       the polarity at the master clock source pin.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

